  "prompt": "How do you simplify \u221a(75yz^2)?",
  "response": "To simplify the expression \\(\\sqrt{75yz^2}\\), follow these steps:\n\n1. **Factor the Radicand:**\n   Break down the number and variables inside the square root into their prime factors.\n   \n   \\[\n   75 = 25 \\times 3 = 5^2 \\times 3\n   \\]\n   \n   So,\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{75yz^2} = \\sqrt{5^2 \\times 3 \\times y \\times z^2}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Separate the Square Factors:**\n   Identify the pairs of factors that are perfect squares.\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{5^2 \\times 3 \\times y \\times z^2} = \\sqrt{5^2} \\times \\sqrt{z^2} \\times \\sqrt{3y}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Simplify the Square Roots of Perfect Squares:**\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{5^2} = 5 \\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\sqrt{z^2} = z\n   \\]\n   \n   So,\n   \n   \\[\n   5 \\times z \\times \\sqrt{3y}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Combine the Terms:**\n   \n   \\[\n   5z\\sqrt{3y}\n   \\]\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{5z\\sqrt{3y}}\n\\]",
